## Key Patterns

### 1. Sending a Message (custom_json - FREE)

```typescript
// In hive.ts
import { broadcastCustomJsonText } from '@/lib/hive';

// Text messages use custom_json (0.000 HBD cost)
await broadcastCustomJsonText({
  from: username,
  to: partnerUsername,
  encryptedPayload: encryptedText,  // Always encrypted via Keychain
  hash: sha256Hash,                  // SHA-256 integrity check
});
```

### 2. Fetching Messages (Hybrid - legacy + new)

```typescript
// Always fetch BOTH types and merge chronologically
const [transferMsgs, customJsonMsgs] = await Promise.all([
  getConversationMessages(user, partner, 200),       // Legacy memo transfers
  getCustomJsonTextMessages(user, partner, 200),     // New custom_json texts
]);
// Merge by txId, sort by timestamp
```

### 3. Decrypting a Message

```typescript
// Check messageType discriminator to pick decryption path
if (message.messageType === 'customJsonText') {
  const plaintext = await decryptTextPayload(encryptedPayload, hash);
} else {
  // Legacy memo
  const plaintext = await decryptMemo(username, encryptedMemo, partner);
}
```

### 4. Encrypting via Keychain

```typescript
// NEVER encrypt manually - always go through Keychain
const sdk = new KeychainSDK(window);
const result = await sdk.encode(username, recipientUsername, message, 'Memo');
// result.result is the encrypted string
```

### 5. Caching Messages

```typescript
import { cacheMessage, cacheMessages, getMessagesByConversation } from '@/lib/messageCache';

// Single message
await cacheMessage(messageCache, username);

// Batch (preferred for performance)
await cacheMessages(messageCacheArray, username);

// Retrieve
const cached = await getMessagesByConversation(username, partnerUsername);
```

### 6. Triggering Fast Polling After Send

```typescript
import { triggerFastPolling } from '@/hooks/useBlockchainMessages';

// Always call this after broadcasting a message
await broadcastMessage(...);
triggerFastPolling(); // Switches to 3-second polling for 15 seconds
```

### 7. Account Metadata (on-chain profile)

```typescript
import { getAccountMetadata, setAccountMetadata } from '@/lib/accountMetadata';

// Read
const metadata = await getAccountMetadata(username);
const minHBD = parseMinimumHBD(metadata);

// Write (broadcasts custom_json to blockchain)
await setAccountMetadata(username, { lightning_address: 'user@getalby.com' });
```

---

## Message Data Model

```typescript
interface MessageCache {
  id: string;                              // txId from blockchain
  conversationKey: string;                 // "userA:userB" (sorted)
  from: string;                            // sender username
  to: string;                              // recipient username
  content: string;                         // decrypted text (or placeholder)
  encryptedContent: string;               // raw encrypted payload
  timestamp: string;                       // ISO 8601 UTC (always 'Z' suffix)
  txId: string;                            // blockchain transaction ID
  confirmed: boolean;                      // always true (no optimistic)
  amount?: string;                         // "0.001 HBD" for legacy
  hidden?: boolean;                        // filtered by minimum HBD
  messageType: 'memo' | 'customJsonText'; // discriminator
  hash?: string;                           // SHA-256 for customJsonText
  isDecrypted?: boolean;                   // true once user decrypted
}
```

---

## Adaptive Polling System

The `useBlockchainMessages` hook uses 4 polling modes:

| Mode | Interval | Trigger |
|------|----------|---------|
| Burst | 3s | Right after user sends (15s window) |
| Active | 5s | Mouse/keyboard activity in last 60s |
| Idle | 15s | No activity for 60+ seconds |
| Background | 45s | Tab hidden (Page Visibility API) |

**React Query config:**
- `staleTime`: 12000ms (serve cached, avoid redundant fetches)
- `gcTime`: 300000ms (5 min memory retention)
- `refetchOnWindowFocus`: 'always' (fresh data on tab return)

---

## Conversation Discovery

```typescript
// discoverConversations scans the user's OWN account history
// The blockchain records all transfers/custom_json involving your account
// So first-contact messages ARE automatically discovered (no follow list needed)

const partners = await discoverConversations(username, 200);
// Returns [{ username: 'alice', lastTimestamp: '...' }, ...]
```

**Two-phase discovery:**
- Phase 1: Last 50 operations (quick, ~5s) → Renders sidebar immediately
- Phase 2: Last 200 operations (full, background) → Fills in older conversations

---

## Custom JSON IDs

```typescript
'hive-messenger-text'   // Text message
'hive-messenger-img'    // Image message (chunked)
'hive-messenger-meta'   // Profile metadata (lightning address, min HBD, etc.)
```

---

## Minimum HBD Filter

- Only applies to **legacy memo-based messages** (`messageType === 'memo'`)
- **custom_json text messages are always visible** (bypass filter)
- Exceptions list (localStorage) whitelists trusted contacts
- Setting stored on-chain: `{ key: 'minimum_hbd', value: '0.010 HBD' }`

---

## RPC Node Management

```typescript
// In hiveClient.ts - Never hardcode a single node
const HIVE_NODES = [
  'https://api.hive.blog',
  'https://api.hivekings.com',
  'https://anyx.io',
  'https://api.openhive.network',
];
// Health scored automatically, failover is transparent
```

